HEADWORD: Turtlehead
<hw>Tur"tle*head`</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧r"t'l-h⟦ecr⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An American perennial herb (<spn>Chelone
glabra</spn>) having white flowers shaped like the head of a turtle.
Called also <altname>snakehead</altname>, <altname>shell
flower</altname>, and <altname>balmony</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

